@node 07943.003
Subject: Re: Rendering to texture
From: Hans-Joerg Frieden <hfrieden@uni-trier.de>
Date: Fri, 01 Oct 1999 14:22:05 +0200

Filip Doksansky wrote:
>  It's possible to render into texture ?
> I had some idea how to create simple LOD based on
> on-the-fly rendered billboards, but it's not
> possible without it...

The only way is to modify the system memory image (i.e your original image
data) and call W3D_UpdateTexImage or W3D_UpdateSubTexImage on it. There is no
way of modifying the video-memory version of a texture. 

The reason for this is quite simple: There is no way of telling what that
texture will look like. The ViRGE has a quite straigtforward texture layout,
but the Permedia 2 has not. Furthermore, it is not sure wether direct video ram
access will always be possible, and newer chips might support a totally
different layout, like S3TC, which cannot be readily updated on the fly.

So this basically means there is no way of supporting direct texture access...
Sorry...

Regards, Hans-Joerg.

