Yup. You have statically initialized structures, including the 'texture'
pointer, but at the time this is assigned, the pointer is still NULL - it
is only assigned *after* the W3D_AllocTexObj is called. You should add a
"triangle.tex = texture" after the call before you draw...

>          triangle ok but no texture?? The image file is in PPM format, what
> does that
>          stand for by the way??

This stands for "Portable Pixmap Format", commonly also referred to as
"P6" because of the two first bytes in the file. PPM is actually a binary
form of P3 files. The "NetPBM" package can create, convert and manipulate
them.

