You have to use patched os-includes. original have got wrong alignment, and
this makes problems on PPC. perl script geninclude.pl from ixemulppc dev
archive will fix includes for you. Also in
ade:ppc-amigaos/include/sys/cdefs.h find a line

#if !defined(__GNUC__) || __GNUC__ < 2 || \
    (__GNUC__ == 2 && __GNUC_MINOR__ < 5)
#define    __attribute__(x)    /* delete __attribute__ if non-gcc or gcc1 */

and remove this define. when gcc is called like this:

ppc-amigaos-gcc -V egcs-2.91.66 

__GNUC__ is set to 'egcs' (should be 2) and this statement delete aligned
atribute.

 Hope this helps.

