Hi

I am writing this mail from my work account, so don't wonder about the missing
signature. Additionally please note, that I have awaited confirmation from the
persons having the responsibility about the WO2097 project, before I wrote this
mail.


In the last few days some posts came in into the 3DWorld mailing list, which
were talking about Wipeout2097, mainly one person was involved in this.

First, it was written that WO2097 for AMIGA was already out, a few days later
it was denied again. Another day afterwards some statements about the
playability and features of WO2097 were posted, inclusive the CD32 joypad
support was mentioned, so there should be no doubt that the AMIGA version
of WO2097 was referred to. Additionally the project was put into the worst
possible light I only can imagine.


Now I want to make the following clear:

******************************************************************************************

The Wipeout2097 AMIGA production release is right now beeing approved by
Psygnosis and has NOT YET BEEN RELEASED.

There is no legal version of Wipeout2097 AMIGA available to the public yet.

We urgently suspect, that early, incomplete and buggy beta versions of the game
have leaked and have been made available by some infamous people. Other sources
have confirmed that there seem to be such versions around. This means that the
AMIGA version of Wipeout2097 referred to in those last posts most likely refer
to illegal versions of the game resp. the beta version of it.

The statements made by people concerning Wipeout2097 AMIGA are in large
parts WRONG and DO NOT REFER to Wipeout2097 AMIGA production release.
Either the people used such a leaked beta version or they are simply talking
nonsense without ever having done any experience.

Wipeout2097 AMIGA production release does support CD32 joypads (and any
other joypads supported by lowlevel.library). It also supports gamma correction
to make the display much brighter (this feature was not available in early beta
versions of the game), which is a special AMIGA feature. And, of course, it
features 10 CD audio tracks and several MPEG animations which contribute to the
great atmosphere a lot. Additionally almost every version before the production
release tended to hang up with some frequency, this problem has been resolved
for production release.


I strictly ask those people which talked about WO2097 AMIGA versions running on
their systems to

********-------------- !!!   S H U T	U P   !!!  ----------------********



I also kindly ask all other people in the 3DWorld mailing list to IGNORE any
talks about apparently existing WO2097 AMIGA versions, until the production
release has been made available. Especially DON'T reply to such posts.
These posts seem only to have the goal of beeing destructive to the Wipeout2097
project, they contain wrong facts and lies.



At this point I want to again remind everyone, that we DON'T TOLERATE people in
this mailing list, which use pirated versions of AMIGA games beeing developed.
Additionally the Warp3D team has made clear, that it is strictly FORBIDDEN to
use Warp3D in conjunction with illegal software. Every violation against this
rule is considered a butt in the face of all those engaged AMIGA developers
working on fantastic projects for the AMIGA, a butt in the face of the Warp3D
