As it's very simple, I'll make it available for all :

          CALLEXEC  Disable   ;should be removed in nonsystem
          lea       $bfe001,a4
          lea       $dff000,a5
          lea       $dff016,a2

          moveq          #7,d5
          bset      d5,$200(a4)
          bclr      d5,(a4)
          move.w         #$6f00,$34(a5)
          moveq          #0,d3
          move.w         #$4000,d1
          moveq          #8,d0
          bra.s          .GoToLoop
.ReadLoop tst.b          (a4)
          tst.b          (a4)
          tst.b          (a4)
.GoToLoop tst.b          (a4)
          tst.b          (a4)
          tst.b          (a4)
          tst.b          (a4)
          tst.b          (a4)
          move.w         (a2),d2
          bset      d5,(a4)
          bclr      d5,(a4)
          and.w          d1,d2
          bne.s          .NoSetBit
          bset      d0,d3
.NoSetBit dbra      d0,.ReadLoop
          move.w         #$7f00,$34(a5)
          bclr      d5,$200(a4)
          CALLEXEC  Enable    ;should be removed in nonsystem
          move.w         d3,d0
          lsr.w          #1,d0

Please note, that those loads of tst.b (a4) isn't bug ;) It's only for
slow down whole code and allow joypad to prepare next bit.
 Anyway it's based on lowlevel.library code.

I don't recommend you to use ANY kind of no-system programming, as it's
incredibly annoying. This is from my 4 years old project (Testament I)

