68k based programs).  The PPC fan that Phase 5 put on the board is a cheap
fan.  It fails after a certain period of time and becomes erratic.  Secondly,
try setting the memory settings for your memory to the "slowest" settings and
see if your problems go away.  If it does, then your memory isn't rated for
what you are running it at (despite what the memory says on itself).  The PPC
board hits memory differently then the IBM's that this memory was made for and
that is what it is rated for.  BUt like I said, it all depends on what
programs you are running.  If they are all shareware/freeware, you might have
