Copy protection mechanisms usually are no solution for the piracy problem.
In contrary, they make the original game less attractive than the pirated
version. Just remember, how things went on in the past: software companies
added fancy copy protection mechanisms and password checks, often the table
was written either in darkgrey font on black ground, or invisible without
special light filters etc. But what's the point of it, if the crackers
simply remove the test against validity? The result is, that the cracked
version doesn't need any password to typed in, and additionally in the
past it was easy to make backup disks of pirated copies, while the original
games often had a protection mechanism which made it impossible to make
a backup.

