You may also create one texture object for every frame in your texture
animation. This will be faster than W3D_UpdateTexImage, as the individual
frames may already be on the graphics board. This will also make use of a
larger video memory if new boards become available. Of course, it means
that other textures may be removed from memory.

Basically, it depends on the amount fo textures you have which way is
faster..

